  <summary date="2017-06-29T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Railroad Yardmaster Protection Act of 2017

This bill applies to yardmaster employees the limitations on duty hours and the restrictions on communications to employees during their off-duty hours that are currently applicable to train employees.

A "yardmaster employee" means an individual responsible for supervising and coordinating the control of trains and engines operating within a rail yard.</summary>
